1
00:00:01,168 --> 00:00:03,670
WHILE TAKATO TRIED TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT WAS UP WITH JERI,

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:05,672
THE MONSTER MAKERS WENT
ON THE AIR TO EXPLAIN

3
00:00:05,672 --> 00:00:07,674
ABOUT THE D-REAPER.
LOOKS LIKE THAT THING HAS BEEN

4
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:08,809
SENDING OUT AGENTS
TO DO ITS DIRTY WORK.

5
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:10,844
THE KIDS GOT
A NOTE FROM THEIR PARENTS

6
00:00:10,878 --> 00:00:13,547
TO GO TO RIKA'S HOUSE, WHERE
THEY ALL GOT SOME COMFORT FOOD

7
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:15,349
AS WELL AS
SOME PARENTAL GUIDANCE.

8
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:17,184
AND THEN IT WAS
OFF TO FACE THE ENEMY.

9
00:00:17,184 --> 00:00:18,685
BUT THE D-REAPER
WAS MORE INTERESTED

10
00:00:18,719 --> 00:00:20,687
IN THIS GIRL ALICE
AND HER FRIEND DOBERMON.

11
00:00:20,721 --> 00:00:23,056
TURNS OUT THE TWO OF THEM
HAD BEEN LOOKING FOR THE TAMERS.

12
00:00:23,123 --> 00:00:24,725
KNOWING THAT THEY COULDN'T
BIOMERGE IN THE REAL WORLD,

13
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:27,494
THE SOVEREIGN SENT DOBERMON
TO DELIVER A MESSAGE

14
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:28,862
AND A GIFT.

15
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,697
I JUST HOPE ALICE
DOESN'T TAKE IT TOO HARD.

16
00:00:31,965 --> 00:00:34,835
DI-DI-DI

17
00:00:34,902 --> 00:00:37,905
DIGIMON, DIGIMON

18
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,742
DI-DI-DIGIMON,
DIGIMON

19
00:00:41,775 --> 00:00:43,377
DI-DI-DI

20
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:45,212
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

21
00:00:45,245 --> 00:00:47,581
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

22
00:00:47,581 --> 00:00:49,416
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

23
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:51,218
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

24
00:00:51,251 --> 00:00:55,889
CHANGE
INTO DIGITAL CHAMPIONS

25
00:00:55,923 --> 00:00:58,492
TO SAVE AND DEFEND THE

26
00:00:58,525 --> 00:00:59,927
WORLD

27
00:00:59,993 --> 00:01:01,695
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

28
00:01:01,762 --> 00:01:04,164
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

29
00:01:04,197 --> 00:01:06,033
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

30
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,468
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

31
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:15,409
DIGIVOLVE
INTO CHAMPIONS

32
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:18,745
DIGIMODIFY

33
00:01:18,779 --> 00:01:20,747
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

34
00:01:20,781 --> 00:01:22,749
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

35
00:01:22,783 --> 00:01:24,751
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

36
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,787
DIGIMON ARE THE CHAMPIONS

37
00:01:26,853 --> 00:01:28,889
DIGIMON --
DIGITAL MONSTERS

38
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,757
DIGIMON

39
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,926
DON'T GO.

40
00:01:32,993 --> 00:01:35,896
I HAVE TO DO THIS, ALICE...

41
00:01:35,929 --> 00:01:37,931
FOR ALL OF US.

42
00:01:41,034 --> 00:01:42,402
[ GASPS ]

43
00:01:42,469 --> 00:01:43,837
THE DIGIMON SOVEREIGN

44
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:46,473
ARE FIGHTING THE ENEMY
IN THE DIGITAL WORLD,

45
00:01:46,473 --> 00:01:48,675
BUT THE ENEMY'S
MOST EVOLVED PART

46
00:01:48,709 --> 00:01:51,979
HAS EMERGED TO WAGE WAR
HERE IN YOUR WORLD.

47
00:01:52,012 --> 00:01:55,349
ONLY YOU, THE TAMERS,
CAN STOP IT

48
00:01:55,382 --> 00:01:58,018
BY FIGHTING AS ONE
WITH YOUR DIGIMON.

49
00:01:58,085 --> 00:02:01,788
TO AID YOU, I BRING A GIFT
FROM THE DIGIMON SOVEREIGN.

50
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:07,260
REMEMBER, THE FATE OF THE WORLD
LIES IN YOUR HANDS!

51
00:02:07,327 --> 00:02:09,429
DOBERMON.

52
00:02:09,496 --> 00:02:10,430
Takato: WHAT'S HAPPENING?

53
00:02:10,497 --> 00:02:11,898
Henry: I CAN'T BE SURE,

54
00:02:11,932 --> 00:02:16,503
BUT I-I THINK HE'S GIVING US
THE POWER TO BIOMERGE.

55
00:02:16,536 --> 00:02:19,573
THEN LET'S DO IT
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

56
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:21,408
DOBERMON'S RIGHT.
WE'RE THE ONLY ONES

57
00:02:21,475 --> 00:02:23,844
WHO HAVE ANY CHANCE
OF SAVING THIS WORLD.

58
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:25,846
WARGROWLMON, LET'S DO IT!

59
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:26,813
RAPIDMON!

60
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:28,148
TAOMON!

61
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,420
[ ALL YELLING ]

62
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:38,722
Takato: [ Thinks ] IF THIS
DOESN'T WORK, WE'RE SUNK.

63
00:02:44,391 --> 00:02:46,026
[ Thinking ] I THINK
I WAS PRETTY SELFISH

64
00:02:46,026 --> 00:02:47,394
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER.

65
00:02:47,394 --> 00:02:48,996
I HAD SO MANY BROTHERS
AND SISTERS,

66
00:02:48,996 --> 00:02:51,832
THE ONLY WAY I COULD BE HEARD
WAS TO ASSERT MYSELF.

67
00:02:51,865 --> 00:02:54,201
WHEN I LEARNED MARTIAL ARTS
FROM SENSEI,

68
00:02:54,234 --> 00:02:55,703
HE TAUGHT ME
THAT WE LEARN TO FIGHT

69
00:02:55,736 --> 00:02:58,138
IN ORDER TO AVOID FIGHTING.

70
00:02:58,172 --> 00:03:00,474
BUT I USED MY POWER
AGAINST A NEIGHBORHOOD KID

71
00:03:00,507 --> 00:03:02,309
AND I HURT HIM.

72
00:03:02,343 --> 00:03:04,978
AFTER THAT, I ALWAYS FELT
LIKE I HAD TO HOLD BACK,

73
00:03:05,045 --> 00:03:06,613
THAT FIGHTING WAS WRONG.

74
00:03:06,647 --> 00:03:08,115
BUT THIS IS DIFFERENT.

75
00:03:08,115 --> 00:03:11,118
THIS IS A BATTLE
THAT MEANS SOMETHING.

76
00:03:14,121 --> 00:03:15,356
FIGHTING FOR A PURPOSE

77
00:03:15,389 --> 00:03:17,791
IS DIFFERENT
THAN JUST FIGHTING TO FIGHT.

78
00:03:19,793 --> 00:03:22,329
THIS IS SOMETHING
I HAVE TO DO --

79
00:03:22,363 --> 00:03:26,200
SOMETHING ONLY TERRIERMON,
MY FRIENDS, AND I CAN DO.

80
00:03:29,837 --> 00:03:32,840
BIOMERGE ACTIVATE!

81
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:37,544
TERRIERMON BIOMERGE TO...

82
00:03:37,611 --> 00:03:40,547
DIGIMON

83
00:03:40,614 --> 00:03:42,049
DI-DI-DIGIMON

84
00:03:44,518 --> 00:03:47,020
DI-DI

85
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:53,660
DI-DI

86
00:03:53,694 --> 00:03:55,629
DI-DI-DIGIMON

87
00:03:58,899 --> 00:04:01,001
MEGAGARGOMON!

88
00:04:07,241 --> 00:04:09,042
[ Thinking ] SOMETIMES
I CAN'T BELIEVE

89
00:04:09,076 --> 00:04:10,711
I'M THE SAME PERSON
WHO ONLY THOUGHT

90
00:04:10,778 --> 00:04:13,547
ABOUT FIGHTING DIGIMON
AND DOWNLOADING THEIR DATA.

91
00:04:13,614 --> 00:04:16,350
BEING THE BEST WAS
THE ONLY THING THAT MATTERED.

92
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:17,551
BUT NOW THAT I'M FRIENDS

93
00:04:17,618 --> 00:04:19,820
WITH HENRY AND TAKATO
AND THE OTHERS,

94
00:04:19,853 --> 00:04:23,023
I REALIZE THAT THERE'S
MORE TO LIFE THAN JUST FIGHTING,

95
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:26,326
AND THAT THERE'S COURAGE
IN FRIENDSHIP, TOO.

96
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:29,163
WHAT MAKES IT TOUGH NOW
IS I HAVE TO WORRY

97
00:04:29,229 --> 00:04:32,099
ABOUT SOMEONE ELSE
BESIDES JUST ME.

98
00:04:32,132 --> 00:04:35,102
NOW I DON'T KNOW
IF I WANT TO FIGHT AT ALL,

99
00:04:35,135 --> 00:04:37,538
SEEING ALL THE PAIN
IT'S CAUSED.

100
00:04:37,571 --> 00:04:40,073
I MEAN, LOOK AT JERI.

101
00:04:42,076 --> 00:04:43,877
BUT THIS ISN'T REALLY
ABOUT FIGHTING.

102
00:04:43,911 --> 00:04:46,747
IT'S ABOUT HAVING THE STRENGTH
TO DO WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE

103
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:48,515
TO SAVE THE WORLD.

104
00:04:50,284 --> 00:04:52,252
BIOMERGE ACTIVATE!

105
00:04:55,255 --> 00:04:57,558
RENAMON BIOMERGE TO...

106
00:04:57,591 --> 00:04:59,927
DIGIMON

107
00:04:59,927 --> 00:05:03,397
DI-DI

108
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:05,432
DIGIMON

109
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:07,568
DIGIMON

110
00:05:07,568 --> 00:05:10,104
DI-DI

111
00:05:10,137 --> 00:05:12,372
DIGIMON

112
00:05:12,406 --> 00:05:15,442
DI-DI

113
00:05:15,476 --> 00:05:18,045
DI-DI-DIGIMON

114
00:05:18,078 --> 00:05:20,280
DI-DI

115
00:05:20,347 --> 00:05:23,450
SAKUYAMON!

116
00:05:23,517 --> 00:05:25,252
DIGIMON

117
00:05:25,285 --> 00:05:28,188
DI-DIGIMON

118
00:05:34,461 --> 00:05:36,296
[ Thinking ] THE FIRST TIME
I BIOMERGED WITH GUILMON,

119
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:38,332
I DIDN'T HAVE A CLUE
WHAT WAS GOING ON.

120
00:05:38,365 --> 00:05:40,501
I MEAN, I ALWAYS KNEW
I HAD AN ACTIVE IMAGINATION,

121
00:05:40,534 --> 00:05:44,338
BUT I NEVER DREAMED
I'D ACTUALLY BECOME A DIGIMON.

122
00:05:44,371 --> 00:05:46,440
BUT THEN WHEN WE MERGED

123
00:05:46,473 --> 00:05:49,142
AND I FELT GUILMON'S STRENGTH
FLOWING THROUGH ME,

124
00:05:49,176 --> 00:05:51,478
IT WAS LIKE A FEELING
OF SAFETY AND STRENGTH

125
00:05:51,512 --> 00:05:53,514
UNLIKE ANYTHING
I'D EVER KNOWN.

126
00:05:53,580 --> 00:05:55,115
THANKS TO HIM,
I KNOW WHAT IT IS

127
00:05:55,149 --> 00:05:58,318
TO FEEL A PART OF SOMETHING
MUCH GREATER THAN MYSELF,

128
00:05:58,352 --> 00:06:01,088
AND NOW THE FATE OF NOT ONE
BUT TWO WORLDS

129
00:06:01,088 --> 00:06:03,023
RESTS ON OUR SHOULDERS.

130
00:06:05,092 --> 00:06:07,628
BUT I KNOW I CAN DO IT
AS LONG AS I HAVE MY FRIEND --

131
00:06:07,661 --> 00:06:09,830
ALL MY FRIENDS --
BY MY SIDE.

132
00:06:09,863 --> 00:06:12,966
NOTHING'S GOING
TO TEAR US APART -- NOTHING.

133
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:19,506
BIOMERGE ACTIVATE!

134
00:06:19,540 --> 00:06:21,008
DI-DI

135
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:23,810
GUILMON BIOMERGE TO...

136
00:06:23,844 --> 00:06:25,979
DI-DI

137
00:06:25,979 --> 00:06:29,483
DI-DI-DIGIMON

138
00:06:29,483 --> 00:06:31,184
DIGIMON

139
00:06:34,154 --> 00:06:36,456
DIGIMON

140
00:06:36,490 --> 00:06:39,560
DI-DI

141
00:06:39,593 --> 00:06:41,528
DIGIMON

142
00:06:41,562 --> 00:06:43,887
GALLANTMON!

143
00:06:43,887 --> 00:06:44,451
Henry: ALL RIGHT,

144
00:06:44,451 --> 00:06:46,053
LET'S SHOW THIS THING
IT CAN'T PUSH US AROUND.

145
00:06:46,053 --> 00:06:49,389
Terriermon: WELL, YOU KNOW,
ANY MORE THAN IT ALREADY HAS.

146
00:06:49,389 --> 00:06:51,725
Guilmon: WE CAN DO ANYTHING
IF WE WORK TOGETHER.

147
00:06:51,725 --> 00:06:53,427
Takato: [ Thinking ]
AND SOMETHING TELLS ME

148
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:54,895
IT'S GOING TO TAKE
EVERYTHING WE'VE GOT.

149
00:07:01,201 --> 00:07:05,339
OH, DOBERMON, I WISH
THERE HAD BEEN MORE TIME.

150
00:07:10,577 --> 00:07:12,512
Takato: WE CAN'T LET
DOBERMON'S GIFT BE IN VAIN.

151
00:07:12,579 --> 00:07:15,882
THE D-REAPER'S GOT
TO BE STOPPED RIGHT NOW.

152
00:07:15,916 --> 00:07:18,485
Guilmon: YOU HEAR THAT,
YOU BIG BALL OF BADNESS?

153
00:07:18,552 --> 00:07:19,987
I'M DRAWING
A LINE IN THE SAND --

154
00:07:20,053 --> 00:07:23,390
WELL, IN THE AIR --
AND YOU WON'T GET PAST IT.

155
00:07:29,262 --> 00:07:31,264
OH, YOU CAME BACK!

156
00:07:31,331 --> 00:07:32,766
[ GIGGLES ]

157
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,234
OH, NO! DON'T GO YET!

158
00:07:34,234 --> 00:07:36,937
NO!

159
00:07:37,004 --> 00:07:39,673
DOBERMON!

160
00:07:46,266 --> 00:07:47,511
AAH!

161
00:07:47,511 --> 00:07:48,846
LIGHTNING JOUST!

162
00:07:52,082 --> 00:07:54,051
YAMAKI -- I MEAN SIR!

163
00:07:54,051 --> 00:07:55,219
LOOK, IT'S THE DIGIMON.

164
00:07:55,252 --> 00:07:57,354
THEY'RE FIGHTING
THE D-REAPER'S AGENTS AGAIN.

165
00:07:57,388 --> 00:07:58,522
THEY'VE COME BACK?

166
00:07:58,555 --> 00:08:00,124
THE CHILDREN --

167
00:08:00,124 --> 00:08:02,826
WE CAN'T JUST LET THEM FIGHT
THAT THING ON THEIR OWN.

168
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:04,828
MEGA BARRAGE!

169
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:13,971
THERE'S GOT TO BE SOME WAY
WE CAN HELP THEM. THINK, GUYS.

170
00:08:14,037 --> 00:08:15,973
HOW'D A BUNCH OF HACKERS

171
00:08:15,973 --> 00:08:17,941
GET MIXED UP
IN SO MUCH TROUBLE

172
00:08:17,975 --> 00:08:20,043
OR CAUSE SO MUCH TROUBLE
FOR OUR CHILDREN?

173
00:08:20,077 --> 00:08:22,179
I'M SORRY, ALICE.

174
00:08:22,212 --> 00:08:24,181
Yamaki: JANYU?
I'VE GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

175
00:08:24,181 --> 00:08:25,382
LIKE WHAT?

176
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:27,851
[ GRUNTS ]

177
00:08:27,885 --> 00:08:31,822
CRYSTAL SPHERE!

178
00:08:31,855 --> 00:08:33,190
MEGA BARRAGE!

179
00:08:36,093 --> 00:08:39,029
[ Thinking ]
GOODBYE, DOBERMON.

180
00:08:39,062 --> 00:08:41,198
YOU DID SOMETHING
NO ONE ELSE COULD --

181
00:08:41,198 --> 00:08:43,033
YOU GAVE THEM A CHANCE.

182
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:44,868
Janyu: I CAN'T JUST STAY HERE!

183
00:08:44,868 --> 00:08:46,437
JANYU,
YOU CAN'T HELP THEM NOW.

184
00:08:46,470 --> 00:08:48,205
WASN'T IT YOU
WHO ALWAYS SAID

185
00:08:48,205 --> 00:08:50,340
THAT EACH PERSON
HAS THINGS THEY MUST DO,

186
00:08:50,374 --> 00:08:52,042
THINGS ONLY THEY CAN DO?

187
00:08:52,042 --> 00:08:55,245
I KNOW,
BUT THEY'RE CHILDREN.

188
00:08:55,245 --> 00:08:58,449
THEY'RE THE ONLY ONES CAPABLE
OF FIGHTING THE D-REAPER.

189
00:08:58,482 --> 00:09:00,184
Man: THE DIGIMON
HAVE RESUMED THEIR ATTACK,

190
00:09:00,184 --> 00:09:02,352
BUT IT IS UNCLEAR
WHO HAS THE UPPER HAND.

191
00:09:02,386 --> 00:09:05,522
AMETHYST WIND!

192
00:09:05,522 --> 00:09:08,058
THE DIGIMON APPEAR
TO BE DOING SOME DAMAGE,

193
00:09:08,092 --> 00:09:10,194
BUT THE DANGER FOR THEM
REMAINS EXTREME.

194
00:09:13,964 --> 00:09:17,000
LIGHTNING JOUST!

195
00:09:17,034 --> 00:09:18,368
AAH!

196
00:09:19,937 --> 00:09:22,005
YOU'VE ALREADY DONE
MORE THAN YOU THINK, JANYU.

197
00:09:22,039 --> 00:09:24,875
YOU HELPED CREATE THE DIGIMON
THAT ARE OUT THERE FIGHTING.

198
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:28,846
WITHOUT YOUR CREATION,
THERE'D BE NO HOPE AT ALL.

199
00:09:28,912 --> 00:09:31,348
AAH!

200
00:09:31,415 --> 00:09:32,749
LET'S GET HIM!

201
00:09:32,749 --> 00:09:34,918
Terriermon: I'M GETTING,
I'M GETTING.

202
00:09:36,954 --> 00:09:38,589
POWER PUMMEL!

203
00:09:38,622 --> 00:09:40,924
YOUR SON AND HIS FRIENDS
ARE LIVING OUT

204
00:09:40,924 --> 00:09:43,060
WHAT YOU ALWAYS
TALKED ABOUT --

205
00:09:43,093 --> 00:09:44,428
DIGIMON AND HUMANS,

206
00:09:44,461 --> 00:09:46,597
BOTH OF THEM
WORKING TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

207
00:09:46,597 --> 00:09:48,599
TRUST IN THEM
TO WIN THE FIGHT.

208
00:09:48,599 --> 00:09:50,267
I DO BELIEVE IN THEM,
IT'S JUST --

209
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:51,635
HE'S MY SON, YAMAKI.

210
00:09:51,702 --> 00:09:53,103
I KNOW.

211
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:55,572
SO USE YOUR WEAPONS
AS A PROGRAMMER TO HELP HIM.

212
00:09:55,606 --> 00:09:57,107
WE NEED YOU HERE.

213
00:09:57,107 --> 00:09:59,409
WELL, THEN WHAT ARE WE
ALL DOING STANDING AROUND?

214
00:09:59,443 --> 00:10:00,978
IF WE'RE GOING
TO STOP THAT THING

215
00:10:00,978 --> 00:10:03,146
OR AT LEAST GIVE THOSE KIDS
A FIGHTING CHANCE,

216
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,982
WE'D BETTER GET HACKING.

217
00:10:04,982 --> 00:10:07,151
THANKS, YAMAKI.

218
00:10:08,886 --> 00:10:10,787
Terriermon: HEY!
DID THAT ACTUALLY WORK?

219
00:10:10,821 --> 00:10:12,689
Henry: [ Sighs ]
OF COURSE NOT.

220
00:10:14,157 --> 00:10:16,226
AAH!

221
00:10:17,861 --> 00:10:19,263
AAH! IT'S GOT US!

222
00:10:21,598 --> 00:10:24,334
Takato: WHY DON'T THE BAD GUYS
EVER JUST STAY DOWN?

223
00:10:24,334 --> 00:10:26,904
I'LL MAKE IT STAY DOWN.

224
00:10:26,937 --> 00:10:28,505
SPIRIT STRIKE!

225
00:10:39,716 --> 00:10:42,219
Rika: IT SEEMS LIKE NO MATTER
HOW MANY OF THOSE THINGS

226
00:10:42,252 --> 00:10:45,355
WE TAKE DOWN,
MORE JUST TAKE THEIR PLACE.

227
00:10:45,389 --> 00:10:46,857
THEN WE'LL KEEP
TAKING THEM DOWN.

228
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:49,226
THE BATTLE RAGES ON
WITH NO CLEAR VICTOR IN SIGHT.

229
00:10:49,259 --> 00:10:51,261
HEY, DAISY,
REMEMBER THE ARK YOU PROGRAMMED

230
00:10:51,328 --> 00:10:53,564
TO BRING THE CHILDREN HOME
FROM THE DIGITAL WORLD?

231
00:10:53,597 --> 00:10:55,199
MM-HMM.

232
00:10:55,232 --> 00:10:56,567
DO YOU THINK
THERE'S ANY WAY

233
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,136
YOU COULD SOMEHOW REESTABLISH
A CONNECTION WITH IT?

234
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,802
I GUESS SO, BUT WHY?
IT'S POWERLESS NOW.

235
00:11:01,836 --> 00:11:03,170
IT CONTACTED ME.

236
00:11:03,170 --> 00:11:03,957
HUH?

237
00:11:03,957 --> 00:11:05,525
THAT'S RIGHT.
I RECEIVED A MESSAGE FROM IT

238
00:11:05,525 --> 00:11:08,161
